1
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:15,500
What's right and what's wrong?

2
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:18,000
I can tell the difference.

3
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:27,980
We can't.

4
00:00:29,670 --> 00:00:31,650
It's fine.

5
00:00:31,650 --> 00:00:34,140
I have a girlfriend, too.

6
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:45,980
I can tell on the inside.

7
00:01:49,420 --> 00:01:53,420
[10 Years Later]

8
00:01:53,420 --> 00:01:55,550
Oh, my.

9
00:01:58,110 --> 00:01:59,530
Gosh.

10
00:02:00,690 --> 00:02:02,510
What is it?

11
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:05,020
Why now?

12
00:02:05,020 --> 00:02:06,005
Okay.

13
00:02:06,005 --> 00:02:07,246
Hello?

14
00:02:07,246 --> 00:02:10,670
Mihono-chan, happy birthday!
[Mom]

15
00:02:10,670 --> 00:02:14,445
Mihono, happy 30th birthday!

16
00:02:14,445 --> 00:02:17,145
Thanks!

17
00:02:17,145 --> 00:02:19,800
I can't believe you're already 30.

18
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,070
Yeah.

19
00:02:21,070 --> 00:02:23,300
Are you celebrating with anyone?

20
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:25,500
That's what you wanted to ask, huh?

21
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:28,740
What's the big deal? It's fine.

22
00:02:28,740 --> 00:02:31,110
I don't have plans. I have work.

23
00:02:31,110 --> 00:02:32,780
Good grief.

24
00:02:32,780 --> 00:02:36,070
If only you'd stayed with Satoshi-kun*. Right?
(*Suffix for young men/colleagues)

25
00:02:36,070 --> 00:02:39,410
Why did you break up with such a nice guy?

26
00:02:39,410 --> 00:02:42,910
Jeez, how long are you going to bring that up?

27
00:02:42,910 --> 00:02:47,390
Oh, hey. Maybe Satoshi-kun is still single too?

28
00:02:47,390 --> 00:02:49,740
He might even text you
a happy birthday today.

29
00:02:49,740 --> 00:02:51,675
- Maybe he will!
- Okay, okay.

30
00:02:51,675 --> 00:02:54,095
Thanks for calling.

31
00:03:04,810 --> 00:03:09,755
[Sales | General Affairs | Accounting]
[Worldrise Travel]

32
00:03:09,755 --> 00:03:11,490
Good morning.

33
00:03:11,490 --> 00:03:14,680
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

34
00:03:15,595 --> 00:03:19,840
Mihono-san*, happy birthday!
(*Polite suffix)

35
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:22,730
What? Thank you, Yuri-chan*!
(*Suffix for cute people)

36
00:03:22,730 --> 00:03:26,470
This is the hand cream I use.
Please give it a try.

37
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:28,820
Wow, I'm so happy.

38
00:03:28,820 --> 00:03:32,990
You're the only person
who truly cares about my birthday.

39
00:03:32,990 --> 00:03:36,230
- That's not true.
- Thank you.

40
00:03:36,230 --> 00:03:40,440
Welcome to Worldrise Travel.

41
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:43,930
Huh? He's super handsome...

42
00:03:45,465 --> 00:03:47,850
Starting today,
I'm joining the sales department.

43
00:03:47,850 --> 00:03:52,898
I'm Eisei Ureshino.
Pleased to meet you all.

44
00:03:52,898 --> 00:03:54,566
Nice to meet you.

45
00:03:57,098 --> 00:03:59,150
Your desk is over here.

46
00:03:59,150 --> 00:04:01,055
Excuse me, pleased to meet you.

47
00:04:01,055 --> 00:04:03,375
Pleased to meet you.

48
00:04:04,350 --> 00:04:05,970
It's fine.

49
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:10,140
I have a girlfriend, too.

50
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:19,920
- Pleased to meet you.
- Pleased to meet you.

51
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,750
Mihono-san?

52
00:04:24,470 --> 00:04:27,040
Are you okay, Mihono-san?

53
00:04:43,195 --> 00:04:46,580
- Sorry, I'm going to make some copies.
- All right.

54
00:04:46,580 --> 00:04:48,460
Work, work...

55
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:52,345
Mihono-san? Are you okay?

56
00:04:52,345 --> 00:04:55,025
- Thanks.
- Here.

57
00:04:55,820 --> 00:04:58,040
You're Onuma-san, right?

58
00:04:58,710 --> 00:05:00,760
No, I'm not.

59
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:06,050
Miporin.

60
00:05:06,763 --> 00:05:08,280
Miporin?

61
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:10,615
Are you talking about Mihono-san?

62
00:05:10,615 --> 00:05:12,385
Oh, yes.

63
00:05:14,170 --> 00:05:16,910
I messed up.

64
00:05:18,050 --> 00:05:21,989
It's obvious now
that I'm conscious of him.

65
00:05:21,989 --> 00:05:28,709
If he finds out I'm still hung up
on something from 10 years ago...

66
00:05:36,845 --> 00:05:38,700
Ureshino-kun, right?

67
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:41,140
You startled me!

68
00:05:41,140 --> 00:05:43,060
We were classmates in college.

69
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:46,060
Oh, I see.

70
00:05:46,060 --> 00:05:49,025
Hey, don't suddenly call me
some weird nickname.

71
00:05:49,025 --> 00:05:52,887
It's been so long
you caught me off guard.

72
00:05:52,887 --> 00:05:57,710
Anyway, I look forward
to working together.

73
00:05:57,710 --> 00:06:01,080
Yeah, me too.

74
00:06:03,810 --> 00:06:06,940
Today, I'm 30 years old.

75
00:06:12,490 --> 00:06:16,180
I've become somewhat of an adult.

76
00:06:19,210 --> 00:06:23,090
♫ It's hard to resist the thing
that I've missed for so long ♫

77
00:06:23,090 --> 00:06:24,830
♫ So long ♫

78
00:06:24,830 --> 00:06:28,650
♫ Can't remember what it's like,
just remember I need it ♫

79
00:06:28,650 --> 00:06:31,050
♫ I need it ♫

80
00:06:31,050 --> 00:06:35,340
♫ You're not what I thought you were ♫

81
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:37,250
♫ You were ♫

82
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:40,640
♫ To think I can't find a cure ♫

83
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:43,180
♫ Find a cure ♫

84
00:06:43,180 --> 00:06:49,310
♫ Ooh, you're not what I thought ♫

85
00:06:52,390 --> 00:06:59,385
[If Only You Weren't the One]

86
00:06:59,385 --> 00:07:02,580
Cheers!

87
00:07:02,580 --> 00:07:05,850
All right, time for self-introductions!

88
00:07:05,850 --> 00:07:07,400
Yeah!

89
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:11,010
Okay, what's your name and ideal type?

90
00:07:11,010 --> 00:07:13,000
Okay! I'm Maki Eto,

91
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,270
and Matsujun from Arashi is my type!

92
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:18,363
Matsujun!

93
00:07:18,363 --> 00:07:20,183
Liar.

94
00:07:20,183 --> 00:07:21,480
Okay, next!

95
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:23,480
Uh, I'm Eisei Ureshino.

96
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:26,060
My ideal type? Hmm...

97
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:29,500
I guess whoever I fall for becomes my type.

98
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:32,050
Ugh, this guy.
That's his go-to line.

99
00:07:32,050 --> 00:07:34,600
Don't fall for it.
Seriously, don't.

100
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,440
- Don't tell them.
- Don't? Oh, sorry!

101
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:38,120
- Okay, next.
- Sure, I'll go next.

102
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:41,462
I'm Numata.
I like kind, family-oriented people.

103
00:07:41,462 --> 00:07:44,927
- Nice to meet you.
- There we go!

104
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:54,430
Man, I drank too much.

105
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:56,980
Ureshino-kun.

106
00:07:56,980 --> 00:07:59,040
What's wrong?

107
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:02,466
Oh, none of them were your type?

108
00:08:02,466 --> 00:08:07,010
No, that's not it.
I actually have a boyfriend.

109
00:08:07,010 --> 00:08:09,828
I was dragged here
to make up the numbers.

110
00:08:09,828 --> 00:08:11,220
So, it's kind of awkward.

111
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:14,675
Oh, really? Me too.

112
00:08:14,675 --> 00:08:16,750
Huh? Really?

113
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:19,040
Yeah. I have a girlfriend, too.

114
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,625
That's why I got tired of it
and stepped outside.

115
00:08:21,625 --> 00:08:24,725
Oh, I see.

116
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:30,520
Oh, then why don't you just pick me?

117
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,730
As the safe choice.

118
00:08:34,535 --> 00:08:36,640
Okay, thanks.

119
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:38,150
No problem.

120
00:08:46,270 --> 00:08:51,040
Hey, so... want to ditch this together?

121
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:53,310
Huh?

122
00:08:54,620 --> 00:08:57,070
I don't want to go back in.

123
00:09:28,203 --> 00:09:29,983
We can't.

124
00:09:36,866 --> 00:09:38,456
It's fine.

125
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:41,720
I have a girlfriend, too.

126
00:09:49,675 --> 00:09:50,800
I really like it.

127
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,945
- Really?
- Yeah.

128
00:09:52,945 --> 00:09:56,580
That homework was tough.
Did you do it?

129
00:09:56,580 --> 00:09:58,310
No.

130
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:08,970
Here, Miporin.

131
00:10:08,970 --> 00:10:10,335
Why?

132
00:10:10,335 --> 00:10:11,885
Cheers.

133
00:10:17,885 --> 00:10:21,840
I came because you said
you wanted work advice.

134
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:24,720
Yeah. Thanks.

135
00:10:25,425 --> 00:10:27,530
You're missing the point.

136
00:10:27,530 --> 00:10:30,255
Why did we meet at a place like this?

137
00:10:30,255 --> 00:10:33,065
Huh? "Like this"?

138
00:10:33,065 --> 00:10:35,560
It looks like a date spot.

139
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:39,850
It's fine, just this once.
We haven't met in a decade.

140
00:10:39,850 --> 00:10:45,655
Oh, tell me all about the company, Senpai*.
(*an experienced colleague)

141
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:51,420
I won't let myself
get swept up by his pace.

142
00:10:53,696 --> 00:10:55,946
Fine, whatever.

143
00:11:01,850 --> 00:11:03,450
Hey.

144
00:11:06,460 --> 00:11:09,970
Don't you feel like this is fate?

145
00:11:14,546 --> 00:11:16,766
I don't.

146
00:11:16,766 --> 00:11:19,640
If this were fate,
we would've worked out 10 years ago.

147
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:22,583
Wow, you're the one who cut off contact.

148
00:11:22,583 --> 00:11:25,368
- Did I?
- You did.

149
00:11:26,710 --> 00:11:31,020
You're the one who didn't choose me.

150
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:33,980
What?

151
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:37,240
No, it's nothing.

152
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:41,750
Thank you for waiting.

153
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:45,430
[Happy Birthday]

154
00:11:47,845 --> 00:11:49,150
Huh?

155
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:51,880
Happy birthday.

156
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:56,320
Huh?

157
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:59,336
Hey, don't look so shocked.

158
00:11:59,336 --> 00:12:01,346
But...

159
00:12:05,980 --> 00:12:09,580
[Happy Birthday]

160
00:12:13,340 --> 00:12:17,370
Open up. Here, say "ah."

161
00:12:22,265 --> 00:12:24,790
- That's good.
- Is it good?

162
00:12:28,673 --> 00:12:30,703
You remembered.

163
00:12:31,420 --> 00:12:33,890
How could I forget?

164
00:12:35,455 --> 00:12:37,980
We celebrated like this before, too.

165
00:12:37,980 --> 00:12:41,560
But this is a slightly upgraded version.

166
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:51,350
Oh, you're blushing.

167
00:12:51,996 --> 00:12:56,936
No, not really. I'm just surprised.

168
00:12:59,950 --> 00:13:01,910
Oh?

169
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:12,195
He's so unrefined...

170
00:13:12,195 --> 00:13:16,840
I'm glad
your boyfriend is working today.

171
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:20,330
That it's addictive.

172
00:13:22,940 --> 00:13:24,970
He's convenient.

173
00:13:28,490 --> 00:13:31,200
Always within reach.

174
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:11,260
Reunion sex with the man
I cheated on 10 years ago.

175
00:16:18,010 --> 00:16:22,040
It's my birthday, and I don't hate him.

176
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:28,200
Well, whatever.

177
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:36,940
I'm single right now.

178
00:16:36,940 --> 00:16:39,240
But what about Ureshino-kun?

179
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:47,870
Well, I guess it's fine.

180
00:16:51,670 --> 00:16:56,650
I'm 30 now. It's different from back then.

181
00:16:59,713 --> 00:17:04,083
Whether it was true love or not...

182
00:17:05,450 --> 00:17:07,600
And 10 years ago,

183
00:17:08,996 --> 00:17:13,606
Wwether I was ever serious
about Eisei Ureshino...

184
00:17:18,540 --> 00:17:22,250
Well, it doesn't matter.

185
00:17:34,830 --> 00:17:38,140
I've done it...

186
00:17:43,155 --> 00:17:45,220
Oh, it's already eight o'clock.

187
00:17:45,220 --> 00:17:48,435
This is the worst.

188
00:17:48,435 --> 00:17:51,939
We can't show up in the same clothes.

189
00:17:51,939 --> 00:17:55,480
See? That hasn't changed.

190
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:58,525
Shut up! Anyway, I'm heading out first.

191
00:17:58,525 --> 00:18:01,245
I'll shower and go to the convenience store.

192
00:18:09,290 --> 00:18:12,130
Good morning.

193
00:18:12,130 --> 00:18:14,130
- Good morning.
- Morning.

194
00:18:14,130 --> 00:18:17,060
Huh? You two came to work together?

195
00:18:17,060 --> 00:18:20,010
- No way!
- We just ran into each other here.

196
00:18:20,010 --> 00:18:24,225
I guess it was... a reunion?

197
00:18:44,805 --> 00:18:48,220
Oh, Mihono-san, that's unusual.
You didn't bring a bento?

198
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:50,490
- Yeah.
- Did something happen?

199
00:18:50,490 --> 00:18:52,799
- Huh?
- Huh?

200
00:18:53,734 --> 00:18:58,130
No, I just thought something came up
since yesterday was your birthday.

201
00:18:58,130 --> 00:19:02,490
Didn't you once say
you had a close friend from college?

202
00:19:02,490 --> 00:19:04,749
Yeah. Something like that.

203
00:19:04,749 --> 00:19:06,925
We just drank a bit too much.
I regret it.

204
00:19:06,925 --> 00:19:10,825
Oh? Nothing wrong with that.

205
00:19:10,825 --> 00:19:12,990
But two nights in a row sounds rough.

206
00:19:12,990 --> 00:19:15,122
Two in a row?

207
00:19:15,122 --> 00:19:19,962
Tonight's welcome party for Ureshino-san
is going to be so fun!

208
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:25,110
Yeah, right.

209
00:19:26,867 --> 00:19:29,030
- It's tonight?
- Yes.

210
00:19:29,030 --> 00:19:31,530
- At the office?
- I think so.

211
00:19:31,530 --> 00:19:33,240
Hmm.

212
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:35,629
Well, then...

213
00:19:37,150 --> 00:19:38,770
Welcome, Ureshino-kun!

214
00:19:38,770 --> 00:19:41,180
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

215
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:43,317
Pleased to meet you!

216
00:19:43,317 --> 00:19:45,140
- Pleased to meet you.
- It's a pleasure.

217
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:46,870
- Cheers.
- Pleased to meet you.

218
00:19:46,870 --> 00:19:49,083
It's a pleasure.

219
00:19:49,083 --> 00:19:51,020
Oh, this is so good.

220
00:19:51,020 --> 00:19:54,415
So, Ureshino-san, are you married?

221
00:19:54,415 --> 00:19:55,820
Well, there's no ring.

222
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:58,010
- I'm not married.
- She was right.

223
00:19:58,010 --> 00:20:01,900
- So, do you have a girlfriend or something?
- Oh?

224
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:03,460
What's this?

225
00:20:03,460 --> 00:20:06,170
Is everyone after me?

226
00:20:06,170 --> 00:20:09,180
Oh, goodness.

227
00:20:09,180 --> 00:20:14,016
- You're all too straightforward.
- It's terrible.

228
00:20:14,016 --> 00:20:15,810
Look at the section chief's face.

229
00:20:15,810 --> 00:20:19,060
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry.

230
00:20:19,060 --> 00:20:21,290
Oh, please, help yourself.

231
00:20:21,290 --> 00:20:22,380
Here you go.

232
00:20:22,380 --> 00:20:24,040
Let's enjoy this.

233
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:26,330
That's mine.

234
00:20:26,330 --> 00:20:27,880
- It's easiest talking to the person next to me.
- Well...

235
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:29,340
Right?

236
00:20:29,340 --> 00:20:32,640
Why don't we make the most out of it?

237
00:21:04,620 --> 00:21:06,140
Section Chief.

238
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:08,510
- How about a second round?
- Of course.

239
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:11,745
- Please do.
- Oh, another round?

240
00:21:11,745 --> 00:21:13,180
A second round, huh?

241
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:14,210
You're going, right?

242
00:21:14,210 --> 00:21:15,955
- Will you go?
- Yes.

243
00:21:15,955 --> 00:21:18,635
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

244
00:21:21,915 --> 00:21:23,500
Want to go for a second round?

245
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:25,330
Oh, Kusaka-kun.

246
00:21:25,330 --> 00:21:27,090
Thanks.

247
00:21:27,090 --> 00:21:28,710
But I'll pass.

248
00:21:28,710 --> 00:21:32,145
I'm a bit tired,
so I'll head home, okay?

249
00:21:32,145 --> 00:21:34,361
I see.

250
00:21:34,361 --> 00:21:36,850
- Oh, sorry!
- Ah, it's fine.

251
00:21:36,850 --> 00:21:40,595
Then, let's go for drinks another time.

252
00:21:40,595 --> 00:21:43,460
Sure. Well, see you.

253
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:45,239
- Please get some good rest.
- Okay.

254
00:21:45,239 --> 00:21:48,144
- Good work today.
- You too.

255
00:22:01,565 --> 00:22:03,760
I'll head out first.

256
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:06,355
Good work today.

257
00:22:06,355 --> 00:22:07,520
You two seem really close.

258
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:09,610
That's right.

259
00:22:23,940 --> 00:22:30,580
♫ We walked through the city at daybreak,
soaked by the rain ♫

260
00:22:30,580 --> 00:22:34,225
♫ You and me in the rain ♫

261
00:22:34,225 --> 00:22:36,110
Want to ditch this together?

262
00:22:36,110 --> 00:22:39,600
- Huh?
- I don't want to go back in.

263
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:45,050
♫ I want to be someone others trust ♫

264
00:22:45,050 --> 00:22:49,720
♫ I kept looking at you ♫

265
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:57,226
♫ Hold me close, stay by my side ♫

266
00:22:57,226 --> 00:22:59,406
What about the second round?

267
00:23:00,260 --> 00:23:03,500
♫ Of my hand ♫

268
00:23:04,540 --> 00:23:06,900
Want to ditch this together?

269
00:23:08,516 --> 00:23:10,086
Let's go.

270
00:23:10,086 --> 00:23:13,110
Huh? Wait!

271
00:23:15,535 --> 00:23:18,110
You're so cute, Miporin. You chased after me.
[Preview]

272
00:23:18,110 --> 00:23:20,290
You tested me? You're the worst.

273
00:23:20,290 --> 00:23:23,430
We're kind of a special pair, aren't we?

274
00:23:23,430 --> 00:23:26,340
I really hate this man.

275
00:23:26,340 --> 00:23:27,580
I hate him so much.

276
00:23:27,580 --> 00:23:31,580
Once you set foot in,
you can't get back out.

277
00:23:31,580 --> 00:23:33,790
Are you asking me out on a date?

278
00:23:33,790 --> 00:23:37,450
If I could fall for someone
like Kusaka-kun, I'm sure...

279
00:23:37,450 --> 00:23:39,150
How about a meal?

280
00:23:39,150 --> 00:23:40,440
Wait for me downstairs.

281
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,665
How about a date tonight?
[This drama is fiction.]

282
00:23:42,665 --> 00:23:44,965
We can't.
[This drama is fiction.]
